## ✅ Working Progress Tracker

The progress bar and step labels are driven by **two simple variables** at the top of the `<script>` section in `maintenance.html`:

```javascript
const STEPS = [
  'Optimization',
  'Running Updates',
  'Deployment',
];

// 👉 Change this number to advance the progress bar:
//    0 = Optimization (first step)
//    1 = Running Updates
//    2 = Deployment
//    3 = All done (100%)
const CURRENT_STEP = 1;
```

### How to update progress

| What you want | Change `CURRENT_STEP` to |
|---|---|
| Starting (Optimization phase) | `0` |
| Running Updates phase | `1` |
| Deployment phase | `2` |
| All done (100% bar) | `3` |

You can also **add/remove/rename steps** by editing the `STEPS` array. The progress bar and labels adjust automatically.

> [!TIP]
> You only need to edit the `CURRENT_STEP` number and re-upload the file to cPanel. No rebuild needed since it's a standalone HTML file.

